openapi generator 7.23.0 comes with option `openApiNullable` that tries to deal correctly with required/nullable keywords applied in Kotlin generated code (here https://github.com/OpenAPITools/openapi-generator/commit/1419ad0871f4ba8c8492b02a72185821f49c6efa)
Unfortunately, it changes the previous `null` property management and it's not fully stable right now.
Fixes and fine-tuning configuration will be apparently available in the next openapi-generator (7.24.0). Until that release, default template dataClassOptVar.mustache is overridden to use option `Nulls.SKIP` instead `Nulls.FAIL` to still accept `null` value for JSON property in endpoint payload.
